TITLE: Berkshire Hathaway's operating earnings jump 20%, conglomerate buys back another $1 billion in stock
SUMMARY: Berkshire Hathaway posted a solid gain in operating profits during the third quarter despite rising recession fears.

TITLE: DraftKings shares tumble after monthly users fall short of estimates
SUMMARY: DraftKings stock fell as much as 26% on Friday despite the sports betting company posting higher-than-expected revenue for its third-quarter earnings report.

TITLE: Take-Two stock tumbles after it cuts outlook
SUMMARY: Take-Two's slashed outlook comes as gaming is a fast cooling businesses after two years of elevated sales and engagement thanks to the Covid-19 pandemic.

TITLE: Palantir stock falls after slight earnings miss
SUMMARY: Shares of Palantir fell Monday after the company released third-quarter earnings that slightly missed analyst estimates for earnings but beat on revenue.

TITLE: Disney misses on profit and key revenue segments, warns streaming growth could taper
SUMMARY: Disney fell short of expectations for profit and key revenue segments during the fiscal fourth quarter Tuesday.

TITLE: Electric vehicle maker Lucid reports third-quarter loss, confirms it's on track to meet production guidance
SUMMARY: The company said it's still on track to make between 6,000 and 7,000 of its luxury sedans this year.

TITLE: Novavax posts third quarter loss but beats revenue expectations
SUMMARY: The Covid-19 vaccine maker reported a net loss of more than $169 million for the third quarter, compared to a loss of $322 million in the same period last year.

TITLE: Lyft shares fall after disappointing revenue, active rider miss
SUMMARY: Lyft reported third-quarter revenue that fell short of estimates, and active riders came in below Wall Street's forecast.

TITLE: Roblox shares sink after reporting bigger loss than expected
SUMMARY: Shares of Roblox fell in premarket trading Wednesday after the company reported a third-quarter loss but beat analyst estimates for revenue.

TITLE: Adidas warns of big earnings hit after ending Ye partnership
SUMMARY: Adidas on Wednesday cut its full-year guidance on the back of the German sportswear giant's termination of its partnership with Kanye West's Yeezy brand.

TITLE: Nio reports strong third-quarter revenue as it gears up for a big year-end production push
SUMMARY: Nio's loss widened significantly from a year ago, but revenue was strong, and the company guided to a big jump in production in the fourth quarter.

TITLE: Rocket Lab reports record quarterly revenue, with added contract wins
SUMMARY: Rocket Lab delivered quarterly results on Wednesday that boasted record revenue, with the space company tacking on additional contract wins across its business.

TITLE: Rivian seeks to cut costs while boosting EV production to meet 2022 targets
SUMMARY: Rivian said it now has "over 114,000" preorders for its R1-series trucks and SUVs.

TITLE: Beyond Meat reports wider-than-expected loss, falling revenue
SUMMARY: Beyond Meat reported a wider-than-expected loss as demand for its meat substitutes tumbled.

TITLE: Swedish EV maker Polestar reports lower operating loss, confirms full-year guidance
SUMMARY: Cost cuts and higher sales helped EV maker Polestar trim its operating loss from a year ago. The company expects to deliver 50,000 vehicles in 2022.

TITLE: Walmart raises outlook as groceries boost sales, inventory glut recedes
SUMMARY: Walmart, the nation's largest grocer, benefited from food sales, as apparel and electronics sales slowed.

TITLE: Home Depot posts better-than-expected quarter despite inflation
SUMMARY: Home Depot reported third-quarter earnings Tuesday, beating analyst expectations.

TITLE: Target shares plunge after retailer reports profit decline, warns of soft holiday quarter
SUMMARY: Target saw sales decline as families contended with higher prices, a potential warning sign for the holiday shopping season.

TITLE: Lowe's says it's not seeing negative impact of inflation as sales, profit top expectations
SUMMARY: Lowe's earnings report comes a day after Home Depot's third quarter earnings beat analysts' estimates.

TITLE: Target warns of soft holiday quarter as profit tumbles and sales slow
SUMMARY: Target saw sales decline as families contended with higher prices, a potential warning sign for the holiday shopping season.

TITLE: Grab pares losses by 24% in third quarter; deliveries segment breaks even earlier than expected
SUMMARY: Grab managed to reduce losses by 24% in the third quarter and broke even in its deliveries segment earlier than expected.

TITLE: Nvidia revenue falls 17% but data center growth remains strong
SUMMARY: Nvidia is closely watched by analysts and investors as a leading indicator for the health of the technology industry.

TITLE: Cisco shares pop on earnings beat and increased 2023 forecast
SUMMARY: Cisco reported fiscal first-quarter results that beat analysts' estimates on top and bottom lines, as the company cited an "easing supply situation."

TITLE: Gap beats on third-quarter revenue, but tempers expectations for holiday season
SUMMARY: Gap on Thursday beat Wall Street's quarterly revenue expectations, but gave a cautious outlook for the holiday season.

TITLE: Zoom shares drop on light forecast as company faces 'heightened deal scrutiny'
SUMMARY: Far from its heady days of 300% growth during the pandemic, Zoom's expansion is mired in the single digits and the company faces headwinds as the economy slows.

TITLE: Best Buy shares rise 10% as retailer sticks with its holiday-quarter outlook
SUMMARY: Best Buy raised its full-year forecast to reflect its better-than-expected quarterly results.

TITLE: Singapore's PropertyGuru slips back into the red with $5.3 million net loss for the third quarter
SUMMARY: "Even with short term macro headwinds, we remain bullish on the long term prospects for PropertyGuru," said Joe Dische, the group's CFO.

TITLE: Shares of Indonesia's GoTo fall 6% as nine-month loss swells
SUMMARY: GoTo said on-demand services, including ride hailing and food delivery, achieved positive contribution margin in September, "several months ahead of schedule."

TITLE: HP laying off 4,000-6,000 employees globally over the next three years
SUMMARY: HP shares moved higher after management announced another wave of job cuts, which come as the company faces steeper revenue declines in PCs and printers.

TITLE: Best Buy shares surge after retailer sticks with its holiday-quarter outlook
SUMMARY: Best Buy raised its full-year forecast to reflect its better-than-expected quarterly results.

TITLE: CrowdStrike shares tumble on weaker-than-expected growth in new revenue
SUMMARY: CrowdStrike shares dropped after the cybersecurity company said annual recurring revenue was below expectations in part because of "macroeconomic headwinds."

TITLE: Snowflake shares drop on light product revenue guidance
SUMMARY: Snowflake shares fell Wednesday after the company released third-quarter results that beat estimates but offered light product revenue guidance.

TITLE: Salesforce stock falls over 5% on earnings and sudden departure of co-CEO Bret Taylor
SUMMARY: Last quarter, Salesforce trimmed its year-end estimates for both revenue and earnings.

TITLE: Ulta Beauty boosts outlook, as shoppers keep splurging on makeup
SUMMARY: Ulta Beauty on Thursday boosted its outlook and surpassed Wall Street's quarterly earnings and sales expectations.

TITLE: MongoDB stock jumps 27% after cloud database company shows surprise adjusted profit
SUMMARY: MongoDB provided upbeat commentary on demand even as some companies are being more cautious with spending on Salesforce and other software.

TITLE: GameStop reports decline in revenue and sharp decrease in cash
SUMMARY: GameStop posted a decline in revenue, but its net loss narrowed from a year ago.

TITLE: GameStop shares rise after earnings report
SUMMARY: GameStop posted a decline in revenue, but its net loss narrowed from a year ago.

TITLE: Rent the Runway shares surge after fashion rental company reports stronger quarterly sales
SUMMARY: The fashion rental company reported stronger revenue that beat expectations as customers opted to borrow designer clothes instead of buying them.

TITLE: TSMC bucks broader chip slump with 50% revenue surge, helped by Apple iPhone orders
SUMMARY: The world's largest contract chipmaker reported the November surge thanks in part to orders of semiconductors for high-end smartphones such as Apple's iPhone.

TITLE: Lululemon shares fall after company offers weak holiday quarter guidance
SUMMARY: Lululemon reported sales and profit that topped estimates, but the company offered softer guidance than expected for the fourth quarter.

TITLE: Oracle beats on top and bottom lines
SUMMARY: Oracle reported better-than-expected results in the fiscal second quarter, as cloud infrastructure revenue jumped.
